    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-01-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-01-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="878"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d878">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/8641</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Beaulac</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 2715</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-01-15">January 15,
                            1940</date>.<lb/>[Received January 16.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    the Department’s telegram No. 3, of January 13, 1940, and to report that I shall
                    take the first opportunity to inform the Cuban Ambassador to Washington in the
                    sense indicated.</p>
                <p>I am sure the Department understands that the Embassy has made every effort to
                    refrain from becoming involved in the present unsatisfactory electoral
                    situation. In accordance with this policy, it has occurred to me—bearing in mind
                    that the Cuban Ambassador to Washington, while personally friendly to General
                    Menocal, is considered by the latter, and particularly by his followers, as a
                    member of the government coalition—that it might become desirable, in the <pb
                        facs="0754" n="742" xml:id="pg_742"/> interest of keeping our Government
                    from becoming involved in this domestic situation, for me to transmit directly
                    to General Menocal, or to Dr. Cuervo Rubio,<note n="12" xml:id="d878fn1">Member
                        of the <hi rend="italic">Partido Demócrata Republicano.</hi>
                    </note> the information contained in the Department’s telegram referred to.</p>
                <p>If the Department agrees, I shall be glad to receive instructions to transmit
                    this information to the persons indicated, should it appear desirable to do
                    so.</p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard L. Beaulac</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
